text: Imma psithyristis is a moth in the family Immidae. It was described by Edward Meyrick in 1906. It is found on the Solomon Islands.Imma at funet.fi. The wingspan is 23–24 mm. The forewings are rather dark purplish-fuscous, strewn throughout with fine pale ochreous-fuscous strigulae and with a dark fuscous discal dot at three-fifths. The hindwings are rather dark fuscous.Trans. Ent. Soc.
